                            <comment id="12689043" author="knutanders" created="Wed, 25 Mar 2009 09:19:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like the problem is caused by the use of eval in bin/dblook, which makes it necessary to escape each special character twice in order to get it to work. Attached is a patch that removes the use of eval and instead uses exec directly. Now the examples mentioned in the bug description work as expected.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12689457" author="knutanders" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2009 11:48:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk with revision 758603.&lt;br/&gt;
Merged to 10.5 and committed revision 758604.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
